The paper deals with the minimum spanning tree problem in the Congested Clique model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves graph algorithms and data structures, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Networks and Networking). The paper also mentions linear graph sketches, which falls under the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper presents new algorithms and bounds, which suggests the category of cs.AL (Computational Complexity).
